item.title: CVE-2021-26621|2024-08-03T20:26:25.557Z -- netu%20corp. -- mex01
item.description: An Buffer Overflow vulnerability leading to remote code execution was discovered in MEX01. Remote attackers can use this vulnerability by using the property that the target program copies parameter values to memory through the strcpy() function.
